WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:19.116 --> 00:00:24.606
We got away from Belorado by a bridge over the Tirón river.

00:00:26.308 --> 00:00:31.928
Tonight was raining too much. The path has a few puddles, but is in good condition.

00:00:33.658 --> 00:00:41.400
The first kilometers of the stage run quiet for a flat track that leads to Tosantos.

00:00:48.070 --> 00:00:54.920
After 6 kilometer walking we reach Tosantos . We are in the region of Montes de Oca.

00:00:58.834 --> 00:01:05.464
It's a small town. The church Virgen de la Peña belongs. We see it on the right.

00:01:07.494 --> 00:01:13.046
We're on the road to Villambistia . The water makes hard the journey by bicycle.

00:01:14.456 --> 00:01:20.618
We visite the hermitage of San Esteban, built in the seventeenth century.

00:01:26.062 --> 00:01:37.634
We find the ruins of the mozarabic Monasterio de San Félix de Oca, built between the sixth and seventh centuries.

00:01:39.004 --> 00:01:43.936
It was a Visigoth work. It was also a refuge for pilgrims.

00:01:45.306 --> 00:01:49.867
From the monastery we can see Villafranca Montes de Oca.

00:01:52.578 --> 00:02:01.941
We walk around the church of Santiago Apóstol and go up into the Montes de Oca. A grueling first kilometer.

00:02:20.782 --> 00:02:29.000
We are surrounded by coniferous and oak . We have to walk 10 kilometers to San Juan de Ortega.

00:02:37.370 --> 00:02:43.310
This long walk trhough  Montes de Oca finish. We went down to the sanctuary of San Juan de Ortega.

00:02:44.996 --> 00:02:52.997
San Juan de Ortega work much in the central apse. Outwardly it is one of the most beautiful Spanish Romanesque.

00:02:53.967 --> 00:03:03.900
San Juan de Ortega began this work in the XII century. He gave his life to help the pilgrims with the construction of bridges and roads.

00:03:05.269 --> 00:03:09.600
Many pilgrims sleep  on this iconic place . The sanctuary takes them for 800 years.

00:03:13.311 --> 00:03:22.910
Another alternative is to continue to Agés, a pretty village which is reached after descending the mountain of Rebollar.

00:03:26.595 --> 00:03:30.997
We are in Agés. Peace and quiet are guaranteed.

